International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>
In this update:
[1] Health Canada West Nile virus surveillance 2003 report, as of 26/27 Aug
2003
[2] Equine case (Ontario ex USA)
******
[1]
Date: Wed 27 Aug 2003
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Health Canada, West Nile Virus Surveillance, Tue/Wed 26/27 Aug 2003
[edited]
<http://www.hc-sc.gc.ca/pphb-dgspsp/wnv-vwn/mon_e.html>

West Nile Virus Surveillance Data as of Tue/Wed 26/27 Aug 2003
--------------------------------------------------------------
Human
-----
As of Tue 26 Aug 2003 there have been a total of 40 probable or confirmed
cases of human infection in Canada, Saskatchewan being the most severely
affected with 28 probable or confirmed cases:
Province/No. probable cases/No. confirmed cases/No. of deaths
Nova Scotia / 1 / 0 / 0
Ontario / 2 / 1 / 0
Manitoba / 2 / 0/ 0
Saskatchewan / 23 / 5 / 0
Alberta / 5 / 1 / 0
Total 33 / 7 / 0
[The probable case in Nova Scotia is considered to be travel-related and
not an indigenous case; see: West Nile virus, human - Canada (Nova Scotia)
ex USA 20030825.2145. Since the last update on Wed 20 Aug 2003 there has
been a more than doubling in the number of cases, with the greatest number
being reported from Saskatchewan. In 2002, there were 416 probable or
confirmed cases of human West Nile virus infection in Canada and 21 deaths
attributed to the virus. All the deaths and most of the cases occurred in
Ontario and Quebec. - Mod.CP]
Equines
-------
As of Tue 26 Aug 2003, 64 presumptive or confirmed equine cases have been
reported; Quebec (4), Ontario (15), Manitoba (14), Saskatchewan (21),
Alberta (10).
[There has been no increase in the number of equine cases of West Nile
virus infection since 20 Aug 2003. The only confirmed case among the 15
equine cases in Ontario is believed to have contracted the infection during
residence in the United States; see [2] below. - Mod.CP]
Mosquitoes
----------
As of Tue 26 Aug 2003, 94 pools of mosquitoes have tested positive; Quebec
(12), Ontario (14), Manitoba (49), Saskatchewan (4), Alberta (15).
[This represents an increase in 67 positive mosquito pools since 20 Aug
2003, with Saskatchewan reporting West Nile virus-positive mosquito pools
(4) for the first time. The biggest increase (38) was recorded by Manitoba.
- Mod.CP]
Wild Birds
----------
As of Wed 27 Aug 2003, the following test Results by Province have been
reported:
Province/No. submitted for testing/No.tested/No. confirmed positive/
Newfoundland and Labrador/ 68/ 63/ 0/
Prince Edward Island/ 245/ 228/ 0/
Nova Scotia/ 695/ 665/ 0/
New Brunswick/ 739/ 694 4/
Quebec/ 1652/ 1547/ 135/
Ontario/ 1541 / 1330/ 116/
Manitoba/ 899/ 804/ 116/
Saskatchewan/ 1178/ 941/ 133/
Alberta/ 1325/ 1308/ 147/
British Columbia/ 1716/ 1687/ 0/
Yukon/ 14/ 13/ 0/
Northwest Territories/ 14/ 14/ 0/
Nunavut/ 2/ 2/ 0/
[The totals for Canada for 2003 so far are 10 088 birds submitted for
testing, 9296 birds tested, and 651 confirmed West Nile virus-positive. In
addition there were 2479 sightings of dead birds recorded. This represents
an increase of 440 birds tested and 1533 more birds confirmed positive
since the last update on Wed 20 Aug 2003. There has been no extension of
range. - Mod.CP]
