[2]
Date: Tue 26 Aug 2003
From: Paul Innes <paul.innes@omaf.gov.on.ca>

Ontario: Confirmed West Nile Virus-positive Equine Case
-------------------------------------------------------
As of Fri 22 Aug, Ontario has one confirmed equine case of West Nile virus
infection [and another 14 presumptive positive cases; see above data -
Mod.CP]. However, given the time of clinical onset (late June) and history
of recent residence in the southern US, the infection is believed to have
been acquired outside of Ontario. The national statistics reported by
Health Canada include all positive test results. Most of the positives
thus far have been positive on IgG ELISA but negative on IgM capture
ELISA. Some of these are believed to be infections from 2002. The Ontario
Ministry of Agriculture and Food (OMAF) will only be reporting newly
acquired confirmed or probable cases, based on clinical history, IgM, PCR
and IHC test results.
--
Paul Innes DVM, MSc
Veterinary Epidemiologist
Ontario Ministry of Agriculture and Food
Fergus ON, Canada
<paul.innes@omaf.gov.on.ca>
